==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heteromorphic
<hw>Het`er*o*mor"phic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <grk>morfh`</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Deviating from the normal, perfect, or mature
form; having different forms at different stages of existence, or in
different individuals of the same species; -- applied especially to
insects in which there is a wide difference of form between the larva
and the adult, and to plants having more than one form of
flower.</def></p>

<p><ent>Heteromorphy</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Heteromorphism</ent>⟦br⟧
